13/04/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- Police arrested six people Tuesday (April 12th) and seized a huge amount of smuggled cigarettes in an operation on the eastern part of the Peloponnese peninsula.
The goods were found in three trucks with Greek, Bulgarian and Italian registration plates.
Officials say they contained 1,700 boxes with 850,000 packs of cigarettes.
In other news Tuesday, three people were arrested on suspicion of stealing explosives from two navy minesweepers.
The explosives were reported missing on April 6th.
The navy says there are no apparent connections to terror activities or organisations.
(Ta Nea, Ethnos, To Vima, ANA-MPA, Zougla, Proto Thema - 12/04/11)
